        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 12:30PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Gusty south to southwesterly winds are already developing over
Beaverhead and portions of Madison counties this afternoon. Wind
gusts will generally run in the 35 to 45 mph range, but gusts may
exceed 50 mph at times, especially near showers and thunderstorms.
Also note the winds will shift to a westerly direction late this
afternoon and evening following a cold frontal passage.

Those with outdoor or travel plans should be prepared for
difficult outdoor recreation and cross winds on area roadways.
Also remember to seek shelter if thunderstorms approach your area.
</description>
